SIMPLE: poundage
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poundage
<hw>Pound"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sum
deducted from a pound, or a certain sum paid for each pound; a
commission.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A subsidy of twelve pence in the pound, formerly
granted to the crown on all goods exported or imported, and if by
aliens, more.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The sum allowed to a sheriff or
other officer upon the amount realized by an execution; -- estimated in
England, and formerly in the United States, at so much of the
pound.</def> <rj><au>Burrill. Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poundage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Poundage
<hw>Pound"age</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To collect, as poundage; to
assess, or rate, by poundage.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poundage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Poundage
<hw>Pound"age</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 3d <er>Pound</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Confinement of cattle, or other animals, in a public
pound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A charge paid for the release of impounded
cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poundal</ent>⟦br⟧
